After experiencing first-hand how difficult it can be to get high-quality, safe, and budget-friendly baby products in Nigeria, Toyin Bajomo did what all moms do - she solved the problem. In 2017, as she was caring for her first child, she launched BabyBliss, a "one-stop-shop" that sells certified, high-quality products for moms and babies. allAfrica's Melody Chironda spoke with Bajomo about BabyBliss's rapid growth, and expansion into Kenya, some challenges that she faces and why more investors should look to Africa.